===Etymology 1===
From earlier {{m|en|len}} (with excrescent ''-d'', as in {{l|en|sound|soun''d''}}, {{l|en|round|roun''d''}}, etc.), from {{inh|en|enm|lenen}}, {{m|enm|lænen}}, from {{inh|en|ang|lǣnan||to lend; give, grant, lease}}, from {{inh|en|gmw-pro|*laihnijan}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*laihnijaną||to loan}}, from {{der|en|gem-pro|*laihną||loan}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*leykʷ-||to leave, leave over}}.

Cognate with {{cog|sco|len}}, {{m|sco|lend||to lend}}, {{cog|fy|liene||to lend, borrow, loan}}, {{cog|nl|lenen||to lend, borrow, loan}}, {{cog|sv|låna||to lend, loan}}, {{cog|is|lána||to lend, loan}}, {{cog|is|léna||to grant}}, {{cog|la|linquō||quit, leave, forlet}}, {{cog|grc|λείπω||leave, release}}. See also {{l|en|loan}}.

